# Git access

Cursor agent shells are allowed to run `git` and `gh` without asking for permission (`~/.cursor/cli-config.json` and `.cursor/cli.json`).

When the user asks to commit or push to **robertcashman-bit** (or any sibling repo):

1. Use normal `git` / `gh` commands in the Shell tool.
2. Do not claim you lack git access.
3. Still follow safety rules: only commit when asked; never force-push to master/main; never skip hooks unless asked.

